{{Infobox musical artist | name = Mr 2Kay | image = | image_size = | landscape = <!-- yes, if wide image, otherwise leave blank --> | alt = | caption = | background = solo_singer | birth_name = Abinye David Jumbo | native_name = Abinye | native_name_lang = | alias = Mr 2Kay | birth_date = <!-- {{birth date and age|df=yes|1986|10|19|1986|10|19} --> | birth_place = [[Port Harcourt]], [[Rivers State]] Nigeria | origin = [[Rivers State]], [[Nigeria]] | death_date = <!-- {{death date and age|df=yes|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date 1st) --> | death_place = | genre = [[Afro pop music]] | occupation = Singer, songwriter, performer | instrument = Vocals | years_active = 2010–present | label = [[Grafton Entertainment]] | associated_acts = Prince Hezekiah, [[Ruggedman]], DJ Joenel, Nanas, Double K, Big Mouf, Sweet Gems, Valo, Hansmills, [[Duncan Mighty]], Aby, Spaceman | website = <!-- {{URL|www.example.com}} --> }}
'''Abinye David Jumbo''' better known as '''Mr 2Kay''', is a [[Nigerian]] singer and songwriter. He is signed to [[Grafton Entertainment]].<ref name="2Kay">{{cite news|title=New Kid from Grafton Records|url=http://www.thisdaylive.com/articles/new-kid-from-grafton-records/109732/|accessdate=12 August 2015|work=Thisday Live|date=21 February 2012}}</ref>
==Early life==
Mr 2Kay was born in [[Port Harcourt]]. After his birth, his family moved to [[Bonny Island]], [[Rivers State]] where he grew up. 2Kay was also a good crafts man as he drew portraits while growing up.<ref>{{cite web|title=Mr 2Kay Biography|url=http://www.biographyhome.com/2014/08/mr-2Kay.html|publisher=Biography Home|accessdate=}}</ref>
Mr 2Kay started his music career in Port Harcourt and his break out single from Port Harcourt was waterside boy but it didn't break international on till 2012 when Mr 2Kay released Bubugaga which was his international break out single.
Mr 2Kay's debut single "Bubugaga" was released on 8 October 2012. The music video for "Bubugaga" was shot in [[London]], [[United Kingdom|UK]] and directed by Nosa Igbinedion under Grafton Entertainment. Which was his international hit single. Mr 2Kay's debut single "Waterside Boy" was released on 21 August 2011 under Grafton Entertainment. Which was his Port Harcourt hit single.<ref>{{cite news|title=Fighting Their Way to Stardom|url=http://allafrica.com/stories/201401061760.html|accessdate=12 August 2015|work=[[AllAfrica]]|date=5 January 2014}}</ref>
==Personal life== ===Robbery Attack=== On 25 October 2017, Mr 2Kay was reportedly robbed by four armed men in his hotel room at [[Eko Hotels and Suites]] at [[Victoria Island, Lagos]] after performing at [[2Baba]]’s Buckwyld and Breathless Concert, which took place at the convention centre of Eko Hotel.<ref>{{cite news|title=Singer,.Mr. 2Kay battered, robbed at gunpoint - Vanguard News|url=https://www.vanguardngr.com/2017/10/singer-mr-2Kay-battered-robbed-gunpoint/|accessdate=8 November 2017|work=Vanguard News|publisher=[[Vanguard (Nigeria)|Vanguard]]|date=25 October 2017}}</ref> 2Kay was left with injuries sustain from the robbery, also totally bound, arms, legs and mouth while the robbers left with his valuables which include, clothes, jewelry, phones, perfumes, and money. 1 week after robbery Mr 2Kay released a new single "Pray for Me" which was scheduled for a late November release alongside with his forthcoming album which is currently on hold due to the incident his label, [[Grafton Entertainment|Grafton Records]] has to push the album release date.<ref>{{cite web|title=Mr. 2Kay - Pray For Me [New Music] {{!}} BellaNaija|url=https://www.bellanaija.com/2017/11/new-music-mr-2Kay-pray/|website=[[BellaNaija]]|accessdate=8 November 2017}}</ref> On 7 November 2017, Mr 2Kay reportedly filed a 500 millionaire lawsuit against the management of [[Eko Hotels and Suites]] where the incident happened in October.<ref>{{cite news|title=ROBBERY ATTACK: Mr 2Kay slams N500m lawsuit on Eko Hotel|url=https://www.ripplesnigeria.com/robbery-attack-mr-2Kay-slams-n500m-lawsuit-eko-hotel/|accessdate=8 November 2017|work=Ripples Nigeria|publisher=Ripples Nigeria|date=7 November 2017}}</ref>
